Dhow
(
Arabic
,
داو
) is the generic name of a number of traditional
sailing vessels
with one or more masts with
lateen sails
used in the
Red Sea
and
Indian Ocean
region. Some historians believe the dhow was invented by
Arabs
but this is disputed by some others.
[
1
]
[
